    How to configure kafka producer in the order service project
order service will act as a producer
we will configure kafka producer in our order service
order service can publish event to the kafka topic
make sure kafka server is running on your local machine
after configuring in the application.properties, start order_service project
    How to create a kafka producer to produce event and send the event to the kafka broker
add base-domains as a dependency in order-service project pom.xml
    create a restApi that will take an order from the client
create an orderController package
    How to configure a consumer in a stock-service, email-service in a micro-service project
This consumers will read the message from the kafka topic.
-go to stock-service application.properties file
spring boot provides auto configuration to configure kafka consumer.
If we have multiple consumers that are consuming the topic, we have to assign the consumers to different groups.
    create a kafka consumer in stock-service project so that stock service can consume or read the message from the kafka topic
run the stock service project and order service project
then go to postman and make a post request to "http://localhost:8080/api/v1/orders"
The order service sends an event to the kafka broker and the stock-service consumes the event/topic
    Email service consumes the order service event from the kafka broker

